'''Epix Pharmaceuticals Inc''' (formerly '''Predix Pharmaceuticals Inc''') was a [[pharmaceutical company]] based in [[Lexington, Massachusetts|Lexington]], [[Massachusetts]].
Its products included the following agents:
* [[PRX-00023]]—[[5-HT1A|5-HT<sub>1A</sub> receptor]] [[full agonist]] (later discovered to be an [[receptor antagonist|antagonist]]): for [[major depression]] and [[generalized anxiety disorder]] * [[PRX-03140]]—[[5-HT4|5-HT<sub>4</sub> receptor]] [[partial agonist]]: for [[Alzheimer's disease]] * [[PRX-07034]]—[[5-HT6|5-HT<sub>6</sub> receptor]] [[receptor antagonist|antagonist]]: for [[obesity]] and [[cognitive impairment]] associated with [[Alzheimer's disease]] and [[schizophrenia]] * [[PRX-08066]]—[[5-HT2B|5-HT<sub>2B</sub> receptor]] [[receptor antagonist|antagonist]]: for [[pulmonary hypertension]] associated with [[chronic obstructive pulmonary disease]]
As of July 2009, the company was in the process of asset liquidation due to insufficient funds to stay afloat.<ref name="urlEpix">{{cite news |url=http://www.boston.com/business/healthcare/articles/2009/07/22/epix_pharmaceuticals_of_lexington_is_latest_biotech_to_fall_to_funding_crunch/ |title=Epix Pharmaceuticals of Lexington is latest biotech to fall to funding crunch |last=Weisman |first=Robert |date=22 July 2009 |newspaper=[[The Boston Globe]] |accessdate=23 November 2011}}</ref>
